All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Administrator
The Administrator class represents an administrator user, extending the User class and implementing the Serializable interface.
Course
The Course class represents a course, implementing the Serializable interface.
CourseEnrollment
The CourseEnrollment class represents a student's enrollment in a course, implementing the Serializable interface.
CourseGroup
The CourseGroup class represents a group within a course, implementing the Serializable interface.
Language
The Language class represents a language with its name, proficiency level, tutors, and available courses.
Level
Enumeration of language proficiency levels.
Operation
Enumeration of operations supported by the system.
Receiver
The Receiver class is responsible for receiving objects over a network connection.
Request
The Request class represents a request to perform an operation, implementing the Serializable interface.
Response
The Response class represents a response, implementing the Serializable interface.
ResponseType
The ResponseType enum represents the type of response.
Sender
The Sender class represents a sender, responsible for sending objects over a socket connection.
Student
Represents a student in the educational system, extending the User class and implementing Serializable.
Tutor
The Tutor class represents a tutor in the language learning system.
User
The User class represents a user in the system.
